{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17591871","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17591871"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:07:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:07:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15215"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15215","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15215"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.22,0.37,0.04,0.04,0.33]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7906"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65379"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7906","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7906"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15215"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50819"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19265"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19268"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21720"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65379","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65379"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIn terms of its global incidence and overall mortality, stomach cancer ranks fifth with some 970,000 new cases being reported in 2022.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following epidemiological points is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Death rates have decreased since 1970","Global prevalence has increased since 1960","Micronesia/Polynesia has the highest incidence in the world","Most cases present before age 50 years","Peak incidence occurs at age 55 years"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edeath rates from gastric adenocarcinoma have decreased significantly since 1970\u003C/strong\u003E, particularly in developed nations. This decline is attributed to improved food preservation methods, reduced \u003Cem\u003EHelicobacter pylori\u003C/em\u003E infection rates, and better diagnosis and treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Epeak incidence of gastric cancer occurs in the seventh decade\u003C/strong\u003E, not at \u003Cstrong\u003Eage 55\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Ebefore age 50\u003C/strong\u003E. The median age at diagnosis is approximately 70 years.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eglobal prevalence of gastric cancer has actually decreased since 1960\u003C/strong\u003E, not increased, though it remains a significant cause of cancer mortality, particularly in East Asia, where the \u003Cstrong\u003Ehighest global incidences are reported from Japan and Korea\u003C/strong\u003E. Micronesia/Polynesia has the least number of stomach cancer cases recorded.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gastric adenocarcinoma death rates have declined significantly over the past 50 years","The mean age of gastric cancer diagnosis is in the seventh decade of life"],"references":["Arnold M, Abnet CC, Neale RE, Vignat J, Giovannucci EL, McGlynn KA, Bray F. Global Burden of 5 Major Types of Gastrointestinal Cancer. Gastroenterology. 2020 Jul;159(1):335-349.e15. doi: 10.1053/j.gastro.2020.02.068. Epub 2020 Apr 2. PMID: 32247694; PMCID: PMC8630546","Goh PMY, Lenzi JE. Benign tumors of the duodenum and stomach. In: Holzheimer RG, Mannick JA, editors. Surgical Treatment: Evidence-Based and Problem-Oriented. Munich: Zuckschwerdt; 2001. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK6948/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Sexton RE, Al Hallak MN, Diab M, Azmi AS. Gastric cancer: a comprehensive review of current and future treatment strategies. Cancer Metastasis Rev. 2020 Dec;39(4):1179-1203. doi: 10.1007/s10555-020-09925-3. Epub 2020 Sep 7. PMID: 32894370; PMCID: PMC7680370."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50819"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15215"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50819","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50819"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-26T13:04:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-26T13:04:52+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7906"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65379"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving inform